There are times, however, when we may need to obtain personally identifiable information from you, such as your name and address. For instance, from time to time, we may conduct on-line surveys to better understand the needs and profile of our visitors. When we collect personally-identifiable information, we will let you know at the time of collection how we will use the personal information. Unless otherwise disclosed to you, the personal information we collect will be used by us (or by one or more of our affiliates) to respond to your inquiry, process business or allow you to access specific account information.
We may use a technology called "cookies" to identify who you are so we can provide you with tailored information. A cookie is a tiny element of data that a web site can send to your browser, which may then be stored on your hard drive so we can recognize you when you return. 
Ambac's web site may contain links to other sites. While we try to link only to sites that share our high standards and respect for privacy, we are not responsible for the content or the privacy practices employed by other sites. 
