Ambac Financial Group, Inc. (AMBC)'s Stock Is Buy After Today's Huge Increase
Xavier Trudeau
Juillet 23, 2017



Part












Wall Street is only getting more bullish on the stock, with 2 of analysts who cover AMBC having a buy-equivalent rating.
MKM Partners "Upgrades" Ambac Financial Grp (NASDAQ:AMBC) in a research note issued to investors on 5/12/17 to Neutral with price target of $0. BTIG Research's price objective would indicate a potential upside of 28.90% from the company's current price.MKM Partners upgraded shares of Ambac Financial Group from a "sell" rating to a "neutral" rating and set a $17.00 target price on the stock in a report on Friday, May 12th. The daily trading volume average remained 0.33 million shares over the course of 3 months. The company's market capitalization is $912.25 million. The stock had opened the regular trading at $21.01 and managed a 18.28% price change to reach $21.22 through the close. Ambac Financial Group has a one year low of $15.67 and a one year high of $27.25. Ambac Financial Group earned a news sentiment score of 0.18 on Accern's scale. The firm had revenue of $126.20 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $136.46 million. During the same period a year ago, the firm posted $4.82 earnings per share. The business's quarterly revenue was down 46.9% compared to the same quarter a year ago.More important recent Ambac Financial Group, Inc.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: This piece was posted by Stock Observer and is owned by of Stock Observer. If you are reading this piece on another website, it was stolen and republished in violation of United States & worldwide copyright legislation. Ambac Financial Group Inc. had 6 analyst reports since August 12, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel.In related news, CEO Claude Leblanc acquired 7,500 shares of the firm's stock in a transaction dated Thursday, May 18th. The shares were acquired at an average cost of $16.45 per share, for a total transaction of $123,375.00. Following the purchase, the chief executive officer now owns 25,400 shares of the company's stock, valued at approximately $417,830. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which can be accessed through this link. Insiders own 1.00% of the company's stock.Several institutional investors have recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Finally, State Street Corp boosted its stake in Ambac Financial Group by 6.7% in the fourth quarter. EJF Capital LLC now owns 1,261,376 shares of the financial services provider's stock worth $23,790,000 after buying an additional 523,550 shares in the last quarter.Ambac Financial Group, Inc. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 2,571,088 shares of the financial services provider's stock worth $57,850,000 after buying an additional 146,075 shares in the last quarter. Seizert Capital Partners LLC purchased a new position in Ambac Financial Group during the first quarter worth $2,657,000.Ambac Financial Group, Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 17.08 and a 200 day moving average of 19.25. Ambac Financial Group's quarterly revenue was down 46.9% on a year-over-year basis. The financial services provider reported ($2.01) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $3.01 by $5.02.

 




